procedures for Tax Division personnel. [Repealed.] CHAPTER 49. CHILD WELFARE. ARTICLE 10. EXEMPTION FROM WEST VIRGINIA DIVISON OF PERSONNEL. §1.  Repeal of article relating to exemption from West Virginia Division of Personnel. That §49-10-101 through §49-10-103 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, are repealed.   NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to repeal provisions of code that exempt the Department of Transportation, the Tax Division, and the Bureau for Social Services from the Division of Personnel.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


